subSubSection.paragraph:
This species is similar to 
Saigona robusta
Liang & Song, 2006, but can be distinguished from the latter by its anal tube rounded in dorsal view (oval in 
robusta
); phallobasal conjunctival processes produced posteriorly (produced dorsally and ventrally, respectively in 
robusta
); phallobase with apical, ventral, membranous lobe small, semi-oval in ventral view (large, triangular in 
robusta
).
